author: COMSOL
description: Surface micromachined thin films are often subject to residual stress. The thermal residual stress is added to a structural mechanical model, which changes the resonant frequency of the structure. This model describes a thin film resonator with folded cantilever beam strings in 2D. The folded flexures relieve axial stress.
label: residual_stress_resonator_2d.mph
